	<td width="98%">
  
		<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="100%">
		<tr>
		    <td valign="top">
		     <p><font face="Verdana" size="3"><b>Article Title:</b>&nbsp;</font>
		     <font face="Verdana" size="2">Morning Abashi posts from the boards</font><br>
		     <a href = "../Subscribe.asp?DID=189677" ><font face="Verdana" size="2">[Subscribe to this document]</font></a></p>
			 </td>
		</tr>
		
		<tr><td>&nbsp;</tr><tr>
		
		    <td valign="top"><div style= "padding:4;float: right"> <script language=JavaScript src=http://www.obsidian-tech.com/absolutebm/abmx.aspx?z=26></script></div><p><font face="Verdana" size="2">
		    <Blockquote>
<B><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum4/HTML/066775.html">As of yet unasked question regarding the new board rules</a></B><P>

Does this mean you'll be paying more attention to the message boards?<P>

<B>While we already pay a *lot* of attention to the boards, I would say that the quality of that attention will improve. I typically read about 20 threads for every one that I can respond to due to the tone of the content. I'd like to see that ratio get much better.</B><P>

How about posts suggesting well thought-out game improvements?<P>

<B>I'd like to give a lot more feedback in this area, even if it is to say that it wouldn't be part of EverQuest. There's a lot of good ideas out there, so many in fact that there's no way we could implement them all. Of course it's no secret that we have several other as-yet-unannounced games in development, and some of those ideas might apply there.</B><P>

Or the post asking for an update to the client software. Even without more spell slots there's still requests for a better hotkey setup, a better system of targeting, easier shop interface, seperate chat boxes for guildchat say or shout. All of these are things commonly found in older and supposedly inferior MUD's.<P>

<B>Incidently, you just may be seeing some improvements in this area over the next couple of months.</B><P>

Will these things get more attention once the trash posts are gone?<P>

<B>Yep, that's certainly the plan. I'll look forward to everyone's help.<P>

-Gordon</B><P>

<HR align="center" width="75%"><P>

<B><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum4/HTML/066777.html">ABASHI..... Board Security</a></B><P>

Have you ever heard of packet sniffers?????<P>

<B>The password exchange is encrypted. The chances of having someone on a subnet capable of sniffing with any success and having sufficient knowledge, hardware, and ability to cause problems in that area is exceedingly low.<P>

-Gordon</B><P>

<HR align="center" width="75%"><P>

<B><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum4/HTML/066779.html">When the board is updated do we login with chat handle or account handle?</a></B><P>

When the board is updated do we login with chat handle or account handle?<P>

<B>You'll need to log in with your station name and password that you use when logging in to EverQuest. Any posts you make from that point forward will automatically use your EverQuest chat handle.<P>

-Gordon</B><P>

<HR align="center" width="75%"><P>

<B><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum4/HTML/066781.html">Abashi : A few yes/no questions.</a></B><P>

1) Do any SK spells cost a PERCENTAGE (%) of the mana bar as opposed to a flat rate of X mana?<P>

<B>All hybrid spells cost more than the stated amount of mana. This difference in cost is greatest at lower levels, and approaches the listed cost at higher levels, though it never quite reaches it.</B><P>

2) Is SK mana INT-based?<P>

<B>Yes, just as ranger and paladin mana is wis-based.</B><P>

3) Does a small race have more mana than a large race, with equal (+50 INT) equipment? (Small races have a higher starting INT.)<P>

<B>No. The amount of mana you have per point of INT is not based upon race.</B><P>

5) In your sole opinion, is the INT bonus of the small races comparable to the str/regen/nostun perks of the large races to make a more viable character? <P>

<B>My *opinion* would be "no". Of course, large races make better SKs, Warriors, etc, as designed. They do pay an additional experience requirement for their race-specific skills and abilities.<P>

-Gordon</B><P>

<HR align="center" width="75%"><P>

<B><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum4/HTML/066945.html">Quick question for Abashi</a></B><P>

After a day is spent browsing this BB, I imagine a person must feel the need to climb out and 'hose himself off'. For this purpose, which do you feel is better: an industrial strength cleanser such as Lava or pumice perhaps, or will commercial soap like Dove or Irish Spring suffice?<P>

<B>Well I used to use pumice, but for some reason it doesn't work as well as it once did :)<P>

On a serious note, we are giving that some thought.<P>

-Gordon</B><P>

<HR align="center" width="75%"><P>

<B><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum4/HTML/066947.html">Tomorrow's downtime</a></B><P>

Wasn't downtime suppost to be annouced with a little more advanced notice? I hope this isn't like last week, remember the 6 hour downtime that ended up being a total of 20 something hours of downtime.<P>

<B>Tomorrow's patch isn't very complex, so I've every confidence that it will go quite well. We're patching the executables and zone data for a few zones.<P>

As for the changes that we are making, I think that people will be quite pleased with them.<P>

-Gordon</B><P>

<HR align="center" width="75%"><P>

<B><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum4/HTML/066953.html">account possibly hacked</a></B><P>

It's really frustrating when you know you typed in the right password but you can't log in... Hackers suck. Verant should hire a band of anti-hackers, hehe..ugh...im sad...... Anyone know of anything I can do (besides call sony that is, i will later)?<P>

<B>I don't think that you were hacked. More likely the server still thinks you are in game, assuming that it's not telling you that you've entered a bad password. Since you've changed your password, that probably isn't likely.<P>

We're putting in some code tomorrow to try and address some of the reports of this nature that we've heard.<P>

-Gordon</B>
</blockquote>
